<h3>1. Optimize your online presence for local SEO</h3>
<p>This isnâ€™t necessarily a trend as Google Business Profiles have been around for 10 years (this year!), but itâ€™s extremely important for any <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/12/15/local-marketing-ideas">local marketing</a> strategy. You still need to master the basics. This means <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/06/03/google-my-business-optimization">optimizing your Google Business Profile</a>, Apple Maps, and other local directories for localâ€”and hyper-localâ€”SEO.</p>
<p>â€œEnsuring your business appears in local search results, particularly your Google Business listing, can significantly increase visibility,â€ said Deepak Shukla, founder of SEO agency <a href="https://pearllemon.com/us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Pearl Lemon</a>. â€œIn the post-pandemic era, where <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/online-presence/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">online presence</a> has become even more critical, this strategy is essential for attracting local customers.â€</p>
<p><a href="https://localiq.com/blog/local-search-marketing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Optimization tactics for local search include</a> the addition of hours, offerings, and reviews, which help <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/09/11/increase-conversion-rates">convert searchers</a> into customers, said Dan Dillon CEO of <a href="https://www.cleanitsupply.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CleanItSupply.com</a>.</p>
