<h3>4. Businesses will launch more immersive experiences</h3>
<p>In a similar vein, expect to see more immersive experiences from brands in 2024.</p>
<p>That includes virtual environments like the metaverse for more interactive experiences, as well as more AR and VR in marketing campaigns for more immersive storytelling.</p>
<p>â€œBrace yourselves for a seamless merger of digital and physical realms,â€ said Neha Gharpande, digital marketing professional at <a href="https://aristasystems.in/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Arista Systems</a>. â€œAugmented reality will play a pivotal role, allowing consumers to virtually experience products before making a purchase. Marketers will need to explore creative ways to leverage AR for immersive brand interactions.â€</p>
<p>Jawa, too, anticipates a â€œsurge in AR-driven campaigns.â€</p>
<p>â€œThis technology will not only enhance customer engagement but also provide more detailed data on customer interactions, which can be used to further refine marketing strategies,â€ he added.</p>
<div id="marketers-become-more-transparent"></div>
<h3>5. Marketers will have to become more transparent</h3>
<p>With 2024 bringing the long-awaited <a href="https://developers.google.com/privacy-sandbox/blog/cookie-countdown-2023oct#:~:text=To%20facilitate%20testing%2C%20Chrome%20has,UK's%20Competition%20and%20Markets%20Authority." target="_blank" rel="noopener">end of third-party cookies</a>, consumer data and privacy will be top of mind as wellâ€”which means even more emphasis on first-party data collection and the continued growth of retail media platforms.</p>
<p>â€œWith heightened concerns about data privacy, marketers will face increasing pressure to prioritize user data protection,â€ Gharpande said. â€œAdhering to stringent <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/11/22/customer-data-privacy" rel="noopener">data regulations</a> and implementing robust security measures will be imperative to foster trust with consumers.â€</p>
<p>It may also include the addition of blockchain technology for additional transparency and securityâ€”particularly in <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/programmatic-advertising">programmatic advertising</a> and to combat ad fraud, Schmied added.</p>
<p>In addition, Sadique expects to see more from the data detox movement, which asks brands to â€œprioritize trust through <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/customer-data/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ethical data collection</a>, clear consent mechanisms, and user-centric personalization.â€</p>
<p>â€œImagine a world where targeted ads are based on preferences explicitly shared by users, rather than shadowy inferences from their browsing history,â€ he added. â€œThis shift necessitates a creative approach to understanding audiences, leveraging declared interests, and opting in [to] data instead of hidden algorithms.â€</p>
<div id="consumers-to-seek-value-oriented-businesses"></div>
<h3>6. Consumers will seek value-oriented businesses</h3>
<p>Another ongoing digital marketing trend expected to retain momentum is a focus on consumer values.</p>
<p>â€œAs societal consciousness continues to grow, consumers will demand more transparency and ethical practices from brands,â€ Gharpande said. â€œDigital marketers will need to champion sustainability and authenticity, weaving these values into their campaigns to establish meaningful connections with conscious consumers.â€</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/earth-day-campaign-example.jpg" alt="example of cause-based marketing campaign on instagram" width="664" height="440" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-79429" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/earth-day-campaign-example.jpg 664w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/earth-day-campaign-example-480x318.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 664px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Schmied agreed, noting, â€œDigital marketing campaigns that highlight a brandâ€™s commitment to sustainability and social responsibility will likely resonate more with audiences.â€</p>
<div id="social-shopping-to-take-off"></div>
<h3>7. Social shopping will take off (even more!)</h3>
<p>Finally, it has taken some time for social commerce to take off in the US, but social media darling TikTok may finally have cracked the code.</p>
<p>According to Toccara Karizma, CEO of <a href="https://www.karizmamarketing.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Karizma Marketing</a>, TikTok social commerce sales hit $53.1 billion in 2023, which is up 34%.</p>
<p>â€œThis growth highlights the platform&#8217;s potential as a lucrative <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/marketing-101" rel="noopener">digital marketing strategy</a> for ecommerce brands in 2024, especially when combined with influencer marketing,â€ she added.</p>
<p>In other words, brands that feature their products on TikTok Shop can work with micro-influencers to extend their reach.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/shoppable-tiktok-ads-example.jpg" alt="shoppable tiktok ads example" width="664" height="419" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-79427" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/shoppable-tiktok-ads-example.jpg 664w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/shoppable-tiktok-ads-example-480x303.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 664px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Gharpande agreed weâ€™ll see social media platforms evolve into full-fledged shopping destinations in 2024.</p>
<p>â€œThe integration of ecommerce features directly into social apps will redefine the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2019/04/25/social-shopping" rel="noopener">online shopping experience</a>,â€ she said. â€œMarketers should capitalize on these trends by creating seamless shopping journeys within social ecosystems.â€</p>
<p>Sadique also expects to see conversational commerce grow thanks to platforms like Shopify and Instagram.</p>
<p>â€œImagine browsing for a new outfit through WhatsApp messages or customizing your dream vacation via voice commands,â€ he said. â€œIn 2024, expect brands to leverage conversational interfaces for frictionless transactions, personalized recommendations, and on-demand customer support.â€</p>
