										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In a March 2023<a href="https://www.gatesnotes.com/The-Age-of-AI-Has-Begun" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> blog post</a>, Microsoft founder Bill Gates described ChatGPT as â€œthe most important advance in technology since the graphical user interfaceâ€ more than 40 years prior.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/chatgpt-marketing-limitations.png" alt="how to use chatgpt for small business marketing - chatgpt limitations" width="720" height="431" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-70681" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/chatgpt-marketing-limitations.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/chatgpt-marketing-limitations-480x287.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>He predicts vast changes in work, education, travel, healthcare, and communication as a result.</p>
<p>The rapid evolution is no less profound for marketers. In just a few short months, the AI-powered tool has found use cases for everything from PPC to SMS marketing and much, much more.</p>
<p>So what does the future hold for the teams tasked with creating the communications that sell our products and services? Will ChatGPT upend the entire marketing industry? Or will its lofty expectations return to earth, leaving it as another useful, but not world-beating, tool like programmatic advertising?</p>
<p>To get a little clarity among the buzz, we asked more than 20 experts for their insights into how ChatGPT will influence four areas of concern for marketers. Hereâ€™s what they told us.</p>
