<h2>How ChatGPT will impact marketing</h2>
<p>Marketers who adopt ChatGPT will soon see sweeping changes in the words, data, and processes they use. Here are some of the most important ways experts predict ChatGPT will impact general marketing.</p>
<h3>Accelerate the content pipeline</h3>
<p>First up is content, which ChatGPT can quickly create to help marketers execute campaigns more efficiently.</p>
<p>This includes blog content, as well as <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/engaging-posts-on-social-media/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">social media posts</a> (although we caution against using it to write your blog content&#8211;more on that later).</p>
<p>â€œThe best part? It won&#8217;t replace you, but rather work alongside you, sort of like a marketing assistant,â€ added Hayley Mollett, marketing coordinator at IT services firm<a href="https://better-it.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Better-IT</a>.</p>
<p>However, Tasos Banioras, digital marketing manager at digital marketing agency<a href="https://tab.gr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Tab.gr</a>, warned marketers must still apply critical thinking when evaluating <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/ai-content-marketing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AI-generated content</a> and ideas.</p>
<p>â€œOtherwise, every marketer will end up with the same or similar ideas,â€ he said.</p>
<p>Instead, marketers should think of ChatGPT as a supplementary tool for content creation. By using ChatGPT to source ideas and inspiration, marketers can make sure their content is helpful, unique, and human.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/chatgpt-impact-ideation.png" alt="" width="893" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-72999 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/chatgpt-impact-ideation.png 893w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/chatgpt-impact-ideation-480x323.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 893px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>Make data and analytics more useful</h3>
<p>Next, ChatGPTâ€™s ability to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2015/01/07/content-marketing-analytics">analyze data and generate insights</a> will be incredibly useful for marketing teams.</p>
<p>â€œIt can help identify trends, predict consumer behavior, and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/02/06/personalized-marketing">personalize marketing messages</a> to a degree that was previously impossible,â€ said Kacper Rafalski, demand generation team leader at the digital consultancy<a href="http://netguru.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Netguru</a>.</p>
<p>Carlos Barros, director of marketing at POS vendor<a href="http://eposnow.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Epos Now</a>, agreed, noting ChatGPT may be able to provide even more insights about a brandâ€™s products and servicesâ€”while Chris Morris, founder of digital marketing agency<a href="http://www.shoosocialmedia.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Shoo Social Media</a>, pointed out it can analyze customer data like purchase history, browsing behavior, and demographics to generate personalized recommendations.</p>
<p>Itâ€™s also a useful market research tool.</p>
<p>â€œChatGPT can analyze customer feedback and social media sentiment to help businesses gain insights into consumer behavior and market trends,â€ Morris added.</p>
<h3>Improve the customerÂ  experience</h3>
<p>Whatâ€™s more, Marc Hardgrove, CEO of SEO platform<a href="http://thehoth.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> The Hoth</a>, noted the <a href="https://www.wordstream.co">AI tool</a> allows marketers to create<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/chatbots" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> customized chatbots</a>, which will change the way brands communicate with customers. That includes the automation of brand responses to basic inquiries and requests.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/ChatGPT-impact-NLP-diagram.jpg" alt="Diagram showing flow of information to and from marketing channels and AI" width="936" height="600" class="aligncenter wp-image-73000 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/ChatGPT-impact-NLP-diagram.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/ChatGPT-impact-NLP-diagram-480x308.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://www.wizeline.com/chatbots/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Â Source</a></em></p>
<p>â€œWith its ability to generate human-like responses, ChatGPT can help businesses engage with their customers in real-time, provide personalized recommendations, and offer a more seamless customer experience,â€ added Rahul Vij, CEO of digital marketing agency<a href="https://www.webspero.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> WebSpero Solutions</a>.</p>
<p>This could improve customer satisfaction and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/03/09/customer-retention-strategies">retention</a>, leading to increased sales, noted Dmytro Sokhach, founder of business development firm<a href="http://admixglobal.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Admix Global</a>.</p>
<h3>End repetitive tasks</h3>
<p>In a similar vein, ChatGPT can simplify additional routine tasks in sales and marketingâ€”like <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2019/09/17/local-lead-generation-strategies">lead generation</a> and nurturingâ€”as well as <a href="https://localiq.com/products/social-media-marketing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">social media management</a>.</p>
<p>This, noted Alexander Hollingsworth, SEO marketing associate at digital agency<a href="http://oyova.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Oyova</a>, â€œ[frees] up time for marketers to focus on more strategic initiatives.â€</p>
