<p>â€œBy knowing what content resonates with customers, small businesses can create more effective marketing strategies,â€ Krasinski added.</p>
<p>This can be helpful when identifying your target audience, personalizing your marketing messages, or looking for new marketing opportunities. But it shouldnâ€™t be the only resource you rely on when it comes to learning about your customers. For now, ChatGPT doesnâ€™t include information <a href="https://www.searchenginejournal.com/openai-chatgpt-update/476116/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">past 2021</a>, so it could be missing a larger piece of the picture when it comes to recommendations or ideas. Learn more about the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/03/06/how-to-use-chatgpt-for-small-business-marketing">pros and cons of ChatGPT for marketing</a> here.</p>
