<h2>How ChatGPT will impact content marketing</h2>
<p>When it comes to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/06/13/content-creation" target="_blank" rel="noopener">content creation</a>, Michelle Burson, president of digital marketing agency<a href="http://marcomm.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> MarComm</a>, suggested likening ChatGPT to the printing press.</p>
<p>â€œMany believed it would put printers out of business, but it didnâ€™t,â€ she said. â€œRather, the printing press enabled printers to work faster, more efficiently and at a lower cost.â€</p>
<p>With that in mind, here are some ways the experts anticipate ChatGPT will impact content marketing.</p>
<h3>Foster ideation</h3>
<p>While marketers may struggle to come up with ideas and keywords on their ownâ€”and therefore miss out on traffic and leads from resulting contentâ€”ChatGPT is a useful tool for <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/05/04/unique-blog-ideas" target="_blank" rel="noopener">brainstorming new topics</a>, as well as gathering data.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Chatgpt-impact-example-research.png" alt="ChatGPT prompt and response asking how Google auction works" width="720" height="818" class="aligncenter wp-image-73002 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Chatgpt-impact-example-research.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Chatgpt-impact-example-research-480x545.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
