<p>â€œChatGPT&#8217;s consolidated responses and speed are a real advantage when it comes to creating helpful content in a more efficient way,â€ said Aissa Djalo of the creative agency<a href="http://tinygiantsco.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Tiny Giants</a>.</p>
<p>ChatGPT can also quickly create content tailored to specific audiences.</p>
<p>â€œBy feeding ChatGPT with information about a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/05/11/target-audience">target audience</a> or customer segment, it can generate content that is more relevant and engaging to that specific group,â€ said Zaira CÃ©spedes, SEO executive at the digital marketing agency<a href="https://ga.agency/en/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> GA Agency</a>.</p>
<p>And, by using ChatGPT for content, brands can maintain a more consistent<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/01/24/editorial-calendar"> publishing schedule</a>â€”and establish themselves as thought leaders, Morris added.</p>
<h3>Require the right prompts</h3>
<p>The key is using the<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/05/08/chatgpt-prompts"> right ChatGPT prompts</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Chatgpt-impact-example-prompt.jpg" alt="chatGPT prompt example" width="936" height="329" class="aligncenter wp-image-73004 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Chatgpt-impact-example-prompt.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Chatgpt-impact-example-prompt-480x169.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Thatâ€™s according to V. Michael Santoro, founder of online branding firm<a href="http://brandvelocity.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Brand Velocity</a>, who said users must follow a process much like optimizing for search results.</p>
<p>â€œWhat&#8217;s important is to instruct ChatGPT to produce the content in the correct voice and writing style based on the brand and messaging,â€ he added. â€œMany new ChatGPT users just request this type of information with, for example, â€˜Write a social media post about ____________.â€™ While the content may be accurate, it may not align with how you want your brand to be perceived in the marketplace.â€</p>
<h3>Be aware of challenges</h3>
<p>Another important takeaway is to adopt ideas from ChatGPTâ€”but not copy and paste them.</p>
<p>Thatâ€™s because ChatGPT may provide the same information to other users, which could result in plagiarism or copyright issues, Santoro said.</p>
<p>In addition, users must always double-check ChatCPT-generated facts with reliable sources.</p>
<p>â€œIt&#8217;s important to note ChatGPT is still a machine learning model, so human oversight and editing are still crucial to ensure the generated content is accurate, appropriate, and consistent with a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/03/31/brand-personality-messaging">brand&#8217;s voice and values</a>,â€ CÃ©spedes said.</p>
<p>Or, as Vladislav Podolyako, CEO of email platform<a href="http://folderly.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Folderly</a>, put it, there are no guarantees ChatGPT-generated answers do not include factual errors.</p>
<p>â€œIt&#8217;s not a problem when you ask what cake recipe tastes better,â€ he said. â€œBut the issue becomes critical when one of the recipes contains rat poison instead of sugar.â€</p>
<p>That means websites with proven information users can trust will be rewarded by search engines.</p>
<h3>Support human writers</h3>
<p>Thereâ€™s also the issue of whether ChatGPT will eventually replace human writers.</p>
<p>For her part, Burson said ChatGPT canâ€™t replace the human experienceâ€”or human capabilities.</p>
<p>The prevailing wisdom, however, seems to be to treat ChatGPT as a companion tool.</p>
<p>â€œWhile too much automation can weaken the human touch that attracts customers, cleverly incorporating it into an overall marketing strategy stands to pay dividends and distinguish brands from their competition,â€ said Jason Tan, founder of LinkedIn assistant<a href="http://engage-ai.co" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Engage AI</a>.</p>
<p>â€œMarketers have the exciting opportunity to unlock AI&#8217;s potential, but understanding what works best requires striking a balance between utilizing technology and allowing human ingenuity to take centerstage.â€</p>
<div id="search"></div>
<h2>How ChatGPT will impact Google search</h2>
<p>Finally, expect to see big changes in both <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/05/19/google-search-generative-experience">how search engines rank content</a>â€”and how brands optimize for SERPs.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Chatgpt-impact-example-GSE.jpg" alt="Screenshot of Google's new Generative Search Experience" width="811" height="599" class="aligncenter wp-image-73005 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Chatgpt-impact-example-GSE.jpg 811w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/Chatgpt-impact-example-GSE-480x355.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 811px, 100vw" /></p>
