<p><a id="privacy"></a></p>
<h2>What changes will we make in privacy?</h2>
<p>In addition to automation, privacy is the other unstoppable force that is carving out new paths in marketing each year. Let&#8217;s see what directions they&#8217;re headed in.</p>
<h3>11. More transparent data practices</h3>
<p>Meanwhile, privacy-friendly reporting dictates marketers must embrace a more transparent approach to data in which users give explicit consentâ€”and, as <a href="https://www.homegrounds.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Home Grounds</a> CEO Alex Mastin noted, they must strike the right balance between personalization and privacy.</p>
<p>To do so, marketers must clearly communicate their <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/11/22/customer-data-privacy">privacy practices</a> to clients and stakeholders and be transparent about the data they are collecting and how it is being used.</p>
<p>They should also use consent management systems and provide clear opt-outs.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/2023-digital-marketing-trends-consent-management.png" alt="2023 digital marketing trends - consent management" width="720" height="317" class="size-full wp-image-69697 aligncenter" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/2023-digital-marketing-trends-consent-management.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/2023-digital-marketing-trends-consent-management-480x211.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>12. Greater adoption of privacy-friendly tracking technology</h3>
<p>â€œAdditionally, they should invest in security tools that allow them to measure performance while still keeping customer data safe from misuse or attack by third parties,â€ Niezgoda said.</p>
<p>But, Sadique noted, marketers can implement privacy-friendly tracking methods, such as using anonymous identifiers or aggregated data, to track and report on key metrics without collecting personal data.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/01/27/google-topics-api">Google&#8217;s Topics API</a>, the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/10/06/facebook-conversions-api">Facebook Conversions API</a>, <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/07/20/facebook-aggregated-event-measurement">Facebook&#8217;s Aggregated Event Measurement</a>, and Google Ads&#8217; Enhanced Conversions are all examples of privacy-friendly technology solutions you can embrace in 2023.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/digital-marketing-trends-2023-enhanced-conversions.png" alt="2023 digital marketing trends - privacy-friendly tracking" width="720" height="449" class="size-full wp-image-69698 aligncenter" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/digital-marketing-trends-2023-enhanced-conversions.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/digital-marketing-trends-2023-enhanced-conversions-480x299.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Boothe agreed, noting it may also involve working with third-party organizations that have expertise in privacy-compliant data management.</p>
<p>â€œMarketers will need to be proactive in finding solutions that balance the need for data with the importance of protecting consumers&#8217; privacy,â€ he added.<br />
<a id="supply"></a></p>
<h2>Will we get a handle on the supply chain?</h2>
<p>Inflation and supply chain shortages were the biggest culprits behind <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/11/10/search-advertising-benchmarks">Google Ads cost per lead increasing in 2022</a>. Here&#8217;s what experts predict on the supply chain front.</p>
<h3>13. More businesses will adopt supply chain automation technology&#8230;</h3>
<p>To protect against the supply chain shortages that plagued the holiday season, businesses can diversify their sourcing, which includes working more with local suppliers, and/or strengthen ties with existing vendors.</p>
<p>They can also implement multi-modal transportation and invest in analytics for greater supply chain visibility and to better anticipate and manage risk.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/2023-digital-marketing-trends-supply-chain-visibility.png" alt="digital marketing trends 2023 - stat about supply chain visibility" width="720" height="405" class="size-full wp-image-69709 aligncenter" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/2023-digital-marketing-trends-supply-chain-visibility.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/2023-digital-marketing-trends-supply-chain-visibility-480x270.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.zippia.com/advice/supply-chain-statistics/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Image source</a></p>
<p>â€œ[Supply chain automation technology] can help to expedite the movement of goods, reduce delays in the supply chain and increase efficiency,â€ Campbell said. â€œAutomation technologies such as robotics, machine learning, big data analysis and artificial intelligence can enable businesses to identify and respond to supply chain disruptions.â€</p>
<h3>14. &#8230;and build prevention and contingency plans</h3>
<p>In addition, building up inventory levels, implementing contingency plans, and looking for opportunities to increase efficiency and reduce costs can help mitigate bottlenecks.</p>
<p>â€œSome businesses may also be considering shifts in their operations, such as moving production to different locations or adopting new technologies, in an effort to reduce their reliance on certain suppliers or markets,â€ Boothe added.</p>
<p>Inventory optimization, which identifies when and where shortages may occur, is another tactic.</p>
<p>â€œAdditionally, businesses may also look to build more robust safety nets, such as insurance policies and emergency funds, to protect them from unexpected economic changes,â€ Shee said.</p>
<h2>Keep an eye on these 2023 marketing trends</h2>
<p>We&#8217;ve covered a lot of trends, patterns, and perspectives in this post, on everything from AI content to supply chain automation. Here is the final list to sum up our top digital marketing trends and predictions for 2023:</p>
<ol>
<li>Some social platforms will imitate or partner with TikTok</li>
<li>Others will distinguish themselves</li>
<li>The advantages of AI content will abound</li>
<li>But human copywriters need not panic</li>
<li>A greater emphasis on equity &amp; intersectionality in the DEI realm</li>
<li>The use of metrics and KPIs for greater DEI accountability</li>
<li>More positive attitudes toward automation</li>
<li>Greater efficiency (but caution) in Google Ads</li>
<li>Catering to Gen Zâ€™s affinity for authenticity, transparency &amp; accessibility</li>
<li>Immersive experiences on social</li>
<li>Increase of transparency in data practices</li>
<li>Greater adoption of privacy-friendly tracking technology</li>
<li>The need for automation technology remains</li>
<li>Building of supply chain prevention and contingency plans</li>
</ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
