					<description><![CDATA[<p>We interviewed over 20 businesses to learn what works for them. Here's what they said!</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/03/09/customer-retention-strategies">13 Customer Retention Strategies to Earn Loyalty (&#038; Save Money)</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Depending on the industry youâ€™re in, acquiring a new customer can be anywhere from <a href="https://hbr.org/2014/10/the-value-of-keeping-the-right-customers" target="_blank" rel="noopener">five to 25</a> times as expensive as simply retaining your existing customers.</p>
<p><a href="https://hbr.org/2014/10/the-value-of-keeping-the-right-customers" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-acquisition-vs-retention-costs.png" alt="customer retention strategies - acquisition vs retention costs" width="525" height="299" class="aligncenter wp-image-58530" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-acquisition-vs-retention-costs.png 525w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-acquisition-vs-retention-costs-480x273.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 525px, 100vw" /></a></p>
<p>That really gets to the heart of why customer retention is so important for all businesses. In this post, we&#8217;re going to take a closer look at this effective marketing strategy, including:</p>
<ul>
<li>What customer retention is and why it&#8217;s important.</li>
<li>How to calculate customer retention rate.</li>
<li>13 customer retention strategies to earn loyalty and save money.</li>
</ul>
<h2>What is customer retention?</h2>
<p>Customer retention is a brandâ€™s ability to keep customers subscribed to or coming back for its products and services. Thatâ€™s according to DavidÂ Morneau, CEO of SEO firm <a href="https://www.breeeze.co/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Breeeze.co</a>, who noted it also prevents customers from switching to competitors.</p>
<h2>Why is customer retention important?</h2>
<p>Repeat customers help ensure a steady flow of income and keep a business stable, said Sherry Morgan, founder of pet site <a href="https://petsolino.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Petsolino</a>. And, in a perfect world, they also help grow a business through <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2014/06/26/word-of-mouth-marketing">positive word-of-mouth marketing</a>.</p>
<p>â€œCustomer retention is one of the best ways to improve your profitability,â€ added consultant <a href="https://www.luisazhou.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Luisa Zhou</a>. â€œMany studies and surveys point to the fact that it&#8217;s far cheaper to keep a customer than to constantly try to find new ones. That&#8217;s because marketing is costly and if you can <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/10/07/customer-engagement-strategy">engage an existing customer</a> so they spend more with you, your profitability increases.â€</p>
<h2><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/cusotmer-retention-strategies-statistics-new-vs-existing.png" alt="customer retention statistics" width="954" height="350" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-58524" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/cusotmer-retention-strategies-statistics-new-vs-existing.png 954w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/cusotmer-retention-strategies-statistics-new-vs-existing-480x176.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 954px, 100vw" /></h2>
<h2>What is customer retention rate?</h2>
<p>Customer retention rate, or CRR, is a <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/marketing-metrics/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">marketing metric</a> that determines how many customers a company retains over a given time period.</p>
<p>â€œIt is one of the most important indicators of <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2016/11/10/customer-loyalty">consumer loyalty</a>,â€ said Jay Bats, developer of social media template firm <a href="https://contentbase.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ContentBase</a>. â€œFor example, if a company starts the year with ten clients and loses two by the end, it has an 80% customer retention rate.â€</p>
<h2>How do you calculate customer retention rate?</h2>
<p>The most common formula for calculating customer retention rate is: CRR = ((E-N)/S) x 100.</p>
<p>According to Geoff Cudd, owner of car buying siteÂ <a href="https://www.findthebestcarprice.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">FindTheBestCarPrice.com</a>, E is the total number of clients you had at the end of a certain time period, N is the number of new clients you gained in this time period, and S is the number of clients you had at the start of this time period. The result is the percentage of clients who remained with you over that time.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retentinon-rate-formula.png" alt="customer retention rate formula" width="600" height="400" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-58531" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retentinon-rate-formula.png 600w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retentinon-rate-formula-480x320.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw" /></p>
<h2>13 customer retention strategies that work</h2>
<p>Whether you&#8217;re a B2C business or <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2016/01/04/client-retention-tips">agency looking to improve your customer retention rate</a>, here are 13 strategies from the experts that work.</p>
<h3>1. Provide a solid customer experience</h3>
<p>It all starts with a good customer experience.</p>
<p>â€œIn today&#8217;s competitive market, exceeding expectations, exceeding customer needs and <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-demonstrate-value-to-your-customers/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">establishing your worth</a> are critical components of success,â€ said Matt Weidle, business development manager of product comparison siteÂ <a href="https://buyersguide.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Buyer&#8217;s Guide</a>. â€œIt is critical your organization maintains customer satisfaction across all channels, including in-person and online encounters.â€</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-example-chewy.png" alt="customer retention strategies - example of chewy" width="400" height="659" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-58532" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-example-chewy.png 400w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-example-chewy-182x300.png 182w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></p>
<p>Take the case of Jeff Neal, founder of <a href="https://www.thecritterdepot.com/products/dubia-roaches-critter-depot" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Critter Depot</a>, who ships live insects to pet stores, zoos, and reptile owners. Retaining customers is very important because of the inherent constraints of its audience size. Thatâ€™s why Critter Depot ships orders quickly, for example.</p>
<p>â€œThe biggest factor is providing good service,â€ he added. â€œSometimes the crickets or roaches will perish in route. It is imperativeÂ that we reship a new order at no cost.Â That one transaction may be a losing proposition for us. However, the long-term potential of retaining that customer greatly salvages the loss on that one order.â€</p>
<blockquote><p>&#8220;That one transaction may be a losing proposition for us. However, the long-term potential of retaining that customer greatly salvages the loss on that one order.&#8221; &#8211; Jeff Neal, Critter Depot</p></blockquote>
<h3>2. Under-promise &amp; overdeliver</h3>
<p>On a related note, itâ€™s wise to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2015/07/15/ppc-agency-pricing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">set customer expectations</a> earlyâ€”and to always exceed them.</p>
<p>â€œBe conservative with your estimates in terms of what you&#8217;ll be able to deliver to your customers. Then, overdeliver on that promise,â€ Zhou said. â€œAlways offer more value than your customer expects. That way, your services/products, no matter what your price point is, become a no-brainer for your customers.â€</p>
<p>RayÂ Blakney, CEO of online language school, <a href="https://www.livelingua.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Live Lingua</a>, agreed even in a highly competitive market, customers are much more likely to return if they have an exceptional experience.</p>
<h3>3. Reward loyalty</h3>
<p>One of the other most obvious <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/customer-retention-strategies-for-small-businesses/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">customer retention strategies</a> is to reward shoppers for their loyalty, such as through a <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-run-customer-loyalty-programs/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">loyalty program</a>.</p>
<p>Rewards can include discounts, gifts, exclusive events, sneak peeks, and more.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-loyalty-program.png" alt="customer retention strategies - rewards program example" width="720" height="457" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-58526" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-loyalty-program.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-loyalty-program-480x305.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>â€œYou have the freedom to be innovative in the kind of loyalty programs you establish and the incentives you provide,â€ said Dustin Porreca, SEO Manager of marketing agency <a href="https://www.elevatedemand.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Elevate Demand</a>. â€œThe bottom line is that you want to make your returning clients feel like VIPs every time they visit your establishment. Allow them to know that they are valued and demonstrate this value via your behaviors so that they will continue to have a reason to return.â€</p>
<p>This, Joanne King, director of online music platformÂ <a href="http://www.icmp-elevate.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ICMP</a>, said, also paves the way for brands to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/05/30/cross-selling-upselling">cross- and upsell</a>.</p>
<blockquote><p>&#8220;Make your returning clients feel like VIPs every time they visit your establishment so that they will continue to have a reason to return.â€ -Dustin Porreca, Elevate Demand</p></blockquote>
<h3>4. Use your data to personalize the experience</h3>
<p>Another way to enhance customer retention is by <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/04/22/how-to-personalize-ecommerce-customer-journey">personalizing the shopping experience</a>. But to do this, you need data.</p>
<p>You can<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/02/17/customer-insights"> collect customer insights</a> through surveys, reviews, purchase behavior, and more, and then create profiles to execute these personalized experiences through deals or messaging.</p>
<p>Per Tyler Martin, business coach atÂ <a href="https://thinktyler.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ThinkTyler</a>, Customer Intelligence Platforms (CIPs) help businesses collect, analyze, and act on customer data to develop customized offerings.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-customer-survey-example.png" alt="customer retention strategies - customer survey example" width="720" height="411" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-58527" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-customer-survey-example.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-customer-survey-example-480x274.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://sightx.io/capabilities/survey" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Image source</em></a></p>
<p>â€œThe more information you have about your clients, the better you will be able to improve their experiences with your company,â€ added Jamie Opalchuk, CEO of web hosting platform <a href="https://www.hostpapa.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">HostPapa</a>. â€œWhen you know who your consumers are, what they need and what their pain points are, you&#8217;ll be in a better position to give them exactly what they need to win their loyalty and return for more transactions with your company.â€</p>
<h3>5. Use live engagement tools</h3>
<p>An easy way to improve the customer experienceâ€”and therefore your customer retention rateâ€”is to respond quickly to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/01/24/customer-feedback">customer feedback</a>, questions, and requests.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-response-times.png" alt="customer retention strategies - response times" width="640" height="372" class="aligncenter wp-image-58533" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-response-times.png 640w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-response-times-480x279.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 640px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.superoffice.com/blog/live-chat-software-benefits/"><em>Data source</em></a></p>
<p>Per David Wurst, CEO of marketing and development agency <a href="https://www.webcitz.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Webcitz</a>, a long response time is one of the primary reasons customers complain of a poor experience.</p>
<p>â€œ<strong>Implementing live chat</strong> can be one of the most effective customer retention strategies,â€ he said. â€œCustomers are 59% more likely to buy if brands respond to their questions in under a minute.â€</p>
<p>In addition, Morgan recommends <strong>sending automated texts or emails</strong> to let customers know the average time for a response.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-channels.jpeg" alt="customer retention strategies - channels used" width="525" height="434" class="aligncenter wp-image-58540" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-channels.jpeg 525w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-channels-480x397.jpeg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 525px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://99firms.com/blog/customer-retention-statistics/#gref" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Image source</em></a></p>
<p>Or, Sep Niakan, managing broker of condo siteÂ <a href="http://condoblackbook.com/">Condoblackbook</a>, noted brands can implement live engagement tools, such as <strong>video chat</strong>, so customer care teams can provide solutions on the first contact.</p>
<p>â€œThe live interaction technologies cut down on client touchpoints and provide efficient responses right away,â€ he said.</p>
<h3>6. Solicit feedback</h3>
<p>Instead of waiting for customers to come with questions, comments or concerns, you can proactively solicit their opinions via feedback mechanisms like customer surveys.</p>
<p>Rohan Kadam, founder of the blog <a href="https://bikingknowhow.com/">Biking Know How</a> recommends <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2014/11/10/best-online-survey-tools">online tools like SurveyMonkey</a> to ask clients about their most recent encounters with your company. â€œI have seen my retention grow from 3% to 27% since using SurveyMonkey,â€ Kadam noted.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-satisfaction-survey-template.png" alt="customer retention strategies - customer satisfaction survey template" width="428" height="340" class="aligncenter wp-image-58534" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>SurveyMonkey offers a <a href="https://www.surveymonkey.com/mp/customer-satisfaction-survey-template/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">survey template</a> to help you get started.</em></p>
<p>Use these surveys to better understand what is and isnâ€™t working in the customer experience.</p>
<p>â€œYou will never be able to please every consumer on every issue, but surveys can help you find patterns that you may have overlooked,â€ said Matthew Paxton, founder of gaming server site <a href="https://hypernia.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hypernia</a>. â€œA good survey should include both multiple-choice questions and free text answer fields to allow customers to express themselves more extensively if necessary.â€</p>
<p>Then, use this feedback to improve your product, service, or experience, said Matt Post, co-founder of web development service <a href="https://wcagpros.com/">WCAG Pros</a>, which specializes in auditingÂ and fixing websites to make them ADA compliant.</p>
<blockquote><p>â€œI have seen my retention grow from 3% to 27% since using SurveyMonkey.â€ -Rohan Kadam, Biking Know HowÂ <em></em></p></blockquote>
<h3>7. Listen online</h3>
<p>Another way to proactively enhance customer retention is through social listening.</p>
<p>â€œSet up and monitor Google alerts and social mentions of your brand in the digital space [and] conduct A/B tests and surveys â€¦ to determine pain points you need to address,â€ said Stacey Kane, business development lead at ecommerce site <a href="https://www.easymerchant.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">EasyMerchant</a>.</p>
<h3>8. Monitor your retention data</h3>
<p>And, of course, customer retention KPIs can also help businesses proactively improve customer retention. Metrics to track here include site traffic, conversions, and abandoned cart ratesâ€”as well as your customer retention rate.</p>
<p>This latter metric measures how loyal customers are, which is especially important in an increasingly crowded market. <strong>An ideal range is 20 to 40%</strong>, said Jason Sherman, CEO of ecommerce platform <a href="https://www.taprm.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TapRm</a>.</p>
<p>â€œYou can improve your [repeat purchase rate] through customer retention strategies such as an <strong>optimized customer life cycle</strong>, <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/brand-loyalty">loyalty programs</a>, <strong>retargeting ads</strong>, and <strong><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2016/03/17/shopping-cart-abandonment">cart abandonment emails</a></strong>,â€ he added. â€œThis creates a better post-purchase experience that drives customer loyalty and increases repeat sales.â€</p>
<p>Neal noted his <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/04/08/how-to-build-an-ecommerce-website">ecommerce website</a> uses <a href="https://www.shopify.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Shopify</a>, which provides retention data like which consumers are returning and how many times those customers order.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-shopify-retention-metrics.png" alt="customer retention strategies - shopify retention metrics dashboard" width="720" height="405" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-58535" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-shopify-retention-metrics.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-shopify-retention-metrics-480x270.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>â€œThey calculate how many of our daily/monthly ordersÂ are completed from repeat customers, which helps us know that our retention rate is growing,â€ he added.<strong>Â </strong></p>
<h3>9. Pay attention to churn</h3>
<p>One specific metric to look out for is <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2014/05/12/customer-churn">churn rate</a>. That includes both performance-related measures, like a decrease in repeat sales or purchase frequency, as well as analyzing each touchpoint in the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/09/19/customer-journey-map-templates">customer journey</a>.</p>
<p>â€œCustomer churn analysis assists stores in analyzing qualitative and quantitative signals from present clients [as well as possible new clients] in order to better understand how to keep them happy with what you&#8217;re doingâ€”making it more likely that other consumers will follow suit,â€ said Rameez Usmani, CMO of <a href="https://webhostingadvices.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Web Hosting Advices.com</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-churn-analysis.png" alt="customer retention strategies - churn analysis" width="720" height="397" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-58541" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-churn-analysis.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-churn-analysis-480x265.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://baremetrics.com/blog/churn-analysis" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Image source</em></a></p>
<p>Greg Gillman, chief revenue officer of performance marketing agency <a href="https://www.mutesix.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MuteSix</a>, noted once you have this model in place, youâ€™ll start to identify patterns that will help predict the probability of churn for each customer.</p>
<p>â€œBut, don&#8217;t stop there,â€ he said. â€œWhen you discover where youâ€™re lagging, adjust acquisition and retention strategies until you see a boost in <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2019/01/10/cac-vs-clv">customer lifetime value</a>.â€</p>
<h3>10. Make onboarding easy &amp; enjoyable</h3>
<p>Part of a good customer experience also requires making the onboarding process as seamless as possible.</p>
<p>â€œWe do this by using auto-login for our member&#8217;s area right after the purchase,â€ said Mark Webster, co-founder of website builderÂ <a href="https://www.authorityhacker.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Authority Hacker</a>. â€œRather than making the customers search through emails and enter login details manually, they are redirected to the course page, which they can use straight away.â€</p>
<p>Paxton agreed a good onboarding process can set you up for long-term success as it makes a good first impression.</p>
<p>â€œIt should be individualized [to the greatest extent possible], hands-on and aimed at removing as much friction as possible,â€ he said.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-onboarding-email.png" alt="customer retention strategies - onboarding email" width="458" height="1035" class="aligncenter wp-image-58538" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://reallygoodemails.com/categories/onboarding" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Image source</em></a></p>
<p>A solid onboarding or <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/08/18/welcome-email">welcome email</a> can make all the difference.</p>
<h3>11. Be transparent</h3>
<p>Another way to enhance customer retention is through transparency. When brands are transparent with consumers, they feel more confident in making future purchases.</p>
<p>â€œWhen you do this, customers know what they need to know about the brand or the product itself. And this gives them a feeling that the brand does not conceal or hide something,â€ said Eddie Bye, founder of supplement site <a href="https://physioflexpro.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Physio Flex Pro</a>. â€œOverall, it is a reliable and fair customer retention strategy both parties could benefit from.â€</p>
<blockquote><p>&#8220;Transparency is a reliable and fair customer retention strategy both parties can benefit from.â€ -Eddie Bye, Physio Flex Pro</p></blockquote>
<h3>12. Use customer relationship management tools</h3>
<p>The good news is you donâ€™t have to juggle all of this aloneâ€”the right <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/11/09/crm-for-small-business">customer relationship management (CRM) platform</a> can help make the process of retaining customers a lot easier.</p>
<p>â€œIt is critical to have a consistent and high-quality dialogue with your customers,â€ said Steve Scott, CTO of Excel tip siteÂ <a href="https://spreadsheetplanet.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Spreadsheet Planet</a>. â€œImplement a CRM system in your business that helps you to maintain an optimal record of your communications with each client and to leverage this information to your advantage.â€</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-crm.png" alt="customer retention strategies - crm" width="480" height="266" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-58537" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-crm.png 480w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-retention-strategies-crm-300x166.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 480px) 100vw, 480px" /></p>
<p>Vishesh Raisinghani, financial expert at personal finance siteÂ <a href="https://piggybank.ca/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PiggyBank</a>, agreed a CRM system can better manage client interactions and help ensure <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/customer-communication/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">effective communication</a> no matter what the channel.</p>
<p>â€œCRM is not just the application of technology, but is a strategy to learn more about customers&#8217; needs and behaviors in order to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/06/21/build-client-relationships">build stronger relationships</a> with them,â€ said Adam Ng, CEO of review site <a href="https://www.trustedmalaysia.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Trusted</a>. â€œThe CRM strategy focuses on putting customer needs first and delivering a superior, more personalized customer experience. Remember one satisfied customer brings ten new customers with him whereas one dissatisfied customer takes away ten customers along with him.â€</p>
<blockquote><p>â€œCRM is not just the application of technology, but a strategy to learn more about customers&#8217; needs and behaviors in order to develop stronger relationships with them.â€ -Adam Ng, Trusted</p></blockquote>
<h3>13. Automate where possible</h3>
<p>Another tool to help keep customers coming back is automation. Paxton pointed to automation systems that simplify entire workflows for marketing teams, which includes re-engaging clients.</p>
<p>â€œRather than requiring your marketing team to track which customers have expired, a marketing automation solution that combines AI and machine learning can automatically recognize when customers lapse and re-engage them with individually relevant content,â€ he said.</p>
<p>King noted this not only saves time and resources, but â€œit also allows you to reach out to several clients at once while maintaining relevant and customized connections.â€</p>
<h2>The 13 best customer retention strategies</h2>
<p>To recap, here are 13 of the best customer retention strategies as determined by the experts interviewed for this post:</p>
<ol>
<li class="p1">Provide a solid customer experience</li>
<li class="p1">Under-promise &amp; overdeliver</li>
<li class="p1">Reward loyalty</li>
<li class="p1">Use your data to personalize the experience</li>
<li class="p1">Live engagement tools</li>
<li class="p1">Solicit feedback</li>
<li class="p1">Listen online</li>
<li class="p1">Monitor your retention data</li>
<li class="p1">Pay attention to churn</li>
<li class="p1">Make onboarding easy</li>
<li class="p1">Be transparent</li>
<li class="p1">Use customer relationship management tools</li>
<li class="p1">Automate where possible</li>
</ol>
