										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>As 2021 draws to a close, weâ€™ll soon see compilations of the best (and worst) marketing campaigns of the year, which will likely include Geicoâ€™s Scoop There It Is ice cream, Nerfâ€™s chief TikTok officer and, of course, Burger King&#8217;s â€œWomen belong in the kitchenâ€ tweet.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/scoop-there-it-is-ice-cream-geico.png" alt="geico's scoop there it is ice cream" class="aligncenter wp-image-53673" width="178" height="237" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/scoop-there-it-is-ice-cream-geico.png 400w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/scoop-there-it-is-ice-cream-geico-225x300.png 225w" sizes="(max-width: 178px) 100vw, 178px" /></p>
<p>These roundups are entertaining and have their takeaways, but from a small business standpoint, they&#8217;re not very useful.</p>
<p>So we sought out to come up with a more<strong> practical best-and-worst round-up for small businesses</strong>. No, you won&#8217;t see any new ice cream flavors in here, but you will find plenty of simple tactics that yielded very gratifying resultsâ€”plus how you can apply them yourself.</p>
<h2>The best of small business PPC</h2>
<p>We asked 20 marketers from a variety of industries for their campaign highs and lows this year. Their answers, which follow, include a range of new and old tactics, as well as the lessons learned from each. Let&#8217;s start with PPC.</p>
<h3><span>1. Countdown ads</span></h3>
<p>Angela Blakenship, CEO of neighborhood comparison site <a href="https://bestneighborhood.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Best Neighborhood</a>, noted adding a countdown timer to Google Ads was â€œa unique PPC campaign strategy that worked really well for us.â€ These ads yielded <strong>higher click-through rates</strong> (CTR) compared to other active campaigns, along with a <strong>higher conversion rate.</strong></p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/google-ads-countdown-timer.png" alt="google ads countdown timer" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-53597" width="720" height="230" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/google-ads-countdown-timer.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/google-ads-countdown-timer-480x153.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>How to apply it</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2016/07/15/ad-customizers-countdown-guide">We show you how to use countdown customizers in Google Ads here</a>. On a broader note, urgency is the tried-and-true element of any good marketing campaign. Check out our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/04/05/how-to-increase-urgency">13 urgency-inducing tricks to drive sales,</a> which include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Super-specific CTAs</li>
<li>Risk-averse payment language</li>
<li>Pre-suasion</li>
</ul>
<h3><span>2. Target CPA + location targeting</span></h3>
<p>Nick Thorsch, founder of <a href="http://share2seed.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Share2Seed.org</a>, a platform that encourages entrepreneurs to think sustainably, said he helped scale revenue for a storage container brand <strong>from $2 million to $10 million</strong> with a campaign that set out to push higher-margin metal containers and refrigerated containers via Google Shopping ads.</p>
<p>He set up unique product pages and pricing to match local markets and used the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/12/19/google-ads-automated-bidding">target CPA</a> bidding strategy, which sought as many customers as possible at a target $100 per conversion.</p>
<p>Thorsch asked sales reps to report the click ID back to Google to measure offline sales. He then expanded to Bing with a similar strategy.</p>
<h3>How to apply it</h3>
<p>There are a few applications here.</p>
<ul>
<li>First, a local strategy is key to any business, even those with global reach, so make sure you know the ins and outs of <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/07/07/google-ads-geotargeting">Google Ads location targeting</a>.</li>
<li>Notice that Thorsch measured offline sales. In our recent Google Ads updates roundup, we cover Google&#8217;s new OCI helper tool (offline conversion import). <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/11/10/google-ads-updates">Check it out!</a></li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/google-ads-oci-helper-tool-dashboard.png" alt="google ads oci helper tool timeline" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-49589" width="720" height="119" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/google-ads-oci-helper-tool-dashboard.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/google-ads-oci-helper-tool-dashboard-480x79.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<ul>
<li>Thorsch was also smart to transfer this strategy over to Bing. We can&#8217;t stress enough the importance of a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2013/10/15/multi-channel-marketing">multi-channel marketing strategy</a>. But do be sure to avoid these <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/08/24/cross-channel-marketing-mistakes">cross-channel marketing mistakes</a>!</li>
</ul>
<h3><span>3. Promotion extensions</span></h3>
<p>Daniel Foley, marketing specialist at vaping site <a href="https://88vape.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">88Vape</a>, tried out promotion extensions on Google to grab visitorsâ€™ attention by highlighting exclusive deals under 88Vapeâ€™s ads. And while he wasnâ€™t expecting much, within a few weeks,<strong> sales of promoted items increased as much as 60%.</strong></p>
<p>â€œThe results were better than what I could have even imagined in my wildest dreams,â€ Foley said. â€œBecause of these tremendous results, it is still running to this day.â€</p>
<h3>How to apply it</h3>
<p>We&#8217;ve talked in the past about how <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/05/24/adwords-promotion-extension">promotion extensions can drive super-high CTR</a>. Learn how to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/05/24/adwords-promotion-extension">use promotion extensions here</a>Â to gain extra visibility and add more appeal to your Shopping ads.</p>
<p>And if applicable, don&#8217;t miss these <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/11/29/google-shopping-promotions">must-know-tips for using promotion extensions during the holiday season.</a><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/05/24/adwords-promotion-extension"></a></p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/google-ads-promotion-extensions.png" alt="google ads promotion extension example" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-53599" width="720" height="324" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/google-ads-promotion-extensions.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/google-ads-promotion-extensions-480x216.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<h2>The best of small business <span>video marketing</span></h2>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/07/23/personalized-video-marketing">Video marketing</a> comes in many shapes and sizes. Find out how two businesses <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/07/29/promote-your-business-on-youtube">used YouTube to promote their business</a> and got better-than-expected results.</p>
<h3><span>4. YouTube live</span></h3>
<p>Jeff Moriarty, creative manager at jewelry retailer <a href="https://www.moregems.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Moriarty&#8217;s Gem Art</a>, said the brand tried out a live show on YouTube this year, which resulted in more than <strong>1,500 viewers</strong> and $10,000 in sales. Now, the retailer hosts live streams once a month. Its Black Friday stream resulted in <strong>$30,000 in sales.</strong> They plan to continue this strategy in 2022.</p>
<p>The brand has a large following on YouTube and sought a solution to reach customers who were no longer will to shop at Moriartyâ€™s brick-and-mortar location.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/youtube-live-example.png" alt="youtube live example" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-53600" width="720" height="322" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/youtube-live-example.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/youtube-live-example-480x215.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCJ-nqExW39TRBF5OH6nnDMw" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Â Image source</em></a></p>
<h3>How to apply it</h3>
<p>You can learn how to run a successful live stream in our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/04/27/youtube-live">guide to going live on YouTube.</a> If YouTube is your bread and butter, consider also building out your channel and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/06/28/youtube-channel-trailer">creating a killer trailer</a> to attract more subscribers. If YouTube isn&#8217;t your channel, you may be interested in <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/07/31/facebook-live-guide">Facebook Live</a> or <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/04/30/instagram-live">Instagram Live</a>.</p>
<h3><span>5. Video targeting tools + influencers</span></h3>
<p>According to Paula Glynn<strong>,</strong> director of search marketing and digital strategy at digital marketing and web development agency <a href="https://pixelstorm.com.au/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Pixelstorm</a>, her most successful PPC campaign was a YouTube campaign focused on products endorsed by celebrities. She used a video targeting tool to overlay ads on videos related to Pixelstormâ€™s partner celebrities. The result was an <strong>ROI of nearly 200%.</strong></p>
<p>â€œYouTube isnâ€™t a platform where PPC shines the best, but it becomes a very efficient strategy through the use of targeting tools,â€ she added.</p>
<h3>How to apply it</h3>
<ul>
<li>Remember, you don&#8217;t have to create video ads to advertise on YouTube! Learn how to run <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/01/29/youtube-display-ads">YouTube display ads</a> here, and how to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/08/17/youtube-ad-placement-targeting">optimize YouTube network and placement targeting here</a>.</li>
<li>There are plenty of video targeting tools out there, outside of the targeting options available in Google Ads.</li>
</ul>
