<h3><span>11. CTA and video embeds</span></h3>
<p>Richard Lubicky, founder of search site <a href="https://realpeoplesearch.com/">RealPeopleSearch</a>, works with a childrenâ€™s clothing brand that wanted to generate leads. He crafted email copy with â€œExpires Tomorrowâ€ as the call to action at the end, along with a video. After a few hours, sales volume increased by 36% versus the prior month. The brand followed up with an offer extension, which <strong>boosted sales volume 42%.</strong></p>
<h3>How to apply it</h3>
<ul>
<li>First and foremost, using &#8220;Expires Tomorrow&#8221; as the CTA is a brilliant idea. You may want to check out these creative <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/10/05/best-call-to-action-phrases">call to action phrases</a>Â to get your customers to act.</li>
<li>Second, whether in your emails or elsewhere, keep your audience engaged with videos! <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2019/11/14/facebook-video-ad">Use a killer hook in your Facebook videos</a>, create <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2016/01/12/memorable-youtube-ads">memorable YouTube video ads</a>, and use <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/12/15/best-video-editing-software-for-beginners">video editing software</a> to polish it off.</li>
