<h2><span>The best of small business prospecting</span></h2>
<p>Just one strategy in this section, with lots of applications.</p>
<h3><span>12. Client conquesting</span></h3>
<p>Brett Downes, marketing manager of digital PR company <a href="https://harohelpers.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Haro Helpers</a>, noted a competitor has a habit of posting the URLs with client mentions on its website daily. He uses this to cross-reference the companies mentioned with the number of mentions to determine which brands are clients. He then reaches out directly to â€œoffer them a better deal.â€ Per Downes, he has a 25%+ success rate when he is able to reach the decision maker. The cost outlay is $500 and <strong>ROI is $50,000</strong> so far.</p>
<h3>How to apply it</h3>
<p>Different <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2019/03/26/prospecting-strategies-ppc-agencies">prospecting strategies</a> work for different businesses. Brett had a very specific opportunity here, but that doesn&#8217;t mean you can&#8217;t find your own. There are a number of tools out there for <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/03/16/marketing-competitive-analysis">competitive analysis</a> that can help with this. Either way, the key is to monitor your competitors&#8217; websites, social media profiles, and ads and be on the lookout for details.</p>
<p>You can use <a href="https://localiq.com/localiq-grader?utm_source=wordstream&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_campaign=freemium" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>LOCALiQ&#8217;s Free Online Presence Grader</strong></a> to get a read on your web, social, and ad presence as well as how you compare to competitors. <img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/localiq-online-presence-grader.png" alt="LOCALiQ free online presence grader screenshot" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-53609" width="720" height="421" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/localiq-online-presence-grader.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/localiq-online-presence-grader-480x281.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<h2><span>The best of small business offline marketing</span></h2>
<p>Offline marketing is considered<a href="https://localiq.com/blog/digital-marketing-vs-traditional-marketing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> &#8220;traditional&#8221; marketingÂ </a>but it is no less important than digital marketing.</p>
<h3><span>13. Community workshops</span></h3>
<p>Web development firm <a href="https://www.websiterating.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Website Rating</a> started offering free home brewing workshops in nearby communities to increase brand awareness. The result was a <strong>3X increase in traffic.</strong></p>
<p>â€œWe are positively obsessed with small businesses and we do go out of our way on our website to help people learn how they can brew their coffee, so our marketing officer suggested this as a content marketing and engagement strategy,â€ said Founder Mathias Ahlgren.</p>
<p>Ahlgren said the moral of the story is â€œas long as you love what you do, you&#8217;ll build communities around your work and it will always be fruitful.â€</p>
<h3>How to apply it</h3>
<p>Tap into the power of event marketing. We have a list of <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/04/25/event-marketing">creative, brand-building event marketing ideas</a> to give you some inspiration. Whatever you choose, consider <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2019/05/21/facebook-ads-for-events">boosting attendance with Facebook ads</a>.</p>
