<p><span lang="EN">Things really are starting to come alive this time around, and your business (and customers) should be too. That&#8217;s why we&#8217;reÂ <span lang="EN">covering seven ways to prepare for and leverage the positive changes to come, according to top digital marketing experts across a variety of industries.</span></span></p>
<h2>1. Return to out-of-home advertising and live events</h2>
<p><span lang="EN">One tactic is to return to <a href="/blog/ws/2020/02/26/out-of-home-advertising">out-of-home advertising</a> and live events, which have understandably been neglected in the last year.Â </span></p>
<p>For his part, Dan Cassidy, CEO of Shopify agency <a href="https://brand-hopper.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Brand Hopper Digital</a>, is advising ecommerce clients to prepare for a boost in demand for products in categories like apparel and beauty â€œthat will help people feel good and look good as they reenter the public.â€</p>
<h3><span lang="EN">Increase your investment in live events</span></h3>
<p><span lang="EN">â€œAfter being cooped up, people are ready to get out into the world and we predict that more people will be traveling, at live events and in public spaces than ever before,â€ said Krista Neher, CEO of digital marketing and social media training program<span lang="EN"> <a href="http://www.bootcampdigital.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Boot Camp Digital</a><span lang="EN">. â€œThis is a great time to capitalize on this.â€</span></span></span></p>
<p><span lang="EN">In fact, she noted Boot Camp Digital plans to increase its investment in live events in order to have a bigger presence when they return.</span></p>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="e8f5f10a-f2cc-4cb7-8088-1cc8105269b0" data-langcode="en">
