<h3><span lang="EN">Reclaim your brand presence</span></h3>
<p><span lang="EN">In a similar vein, industries that have struggled during the pandemicâ€”events included, along with travelâ€”should brace for comebacks.</span></p>
<p><span lang="EN">Per Andrei Vasilescu, CEO of coupon site<span lang="EN"> <a href="http://www.dontpayfull.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">DontPayFull</a><span lang="EN">, that means focusing on recall.</span></span></span></p>
<p><span lang="EN">â€œThey have to re-establish their brand existence in the market,â€ he said. â€œBusinesses must reclaim their <a href="/blog/ws/2021/02/01/brand-strategy">brand presence</a> in order to regain their consumers in 2021.â€</span></p>
<h2>2. Adjust brand messaging to be more empathetic</h2>
<p><span lang="EN">After a challenging year in many respects, <a href="/blog/ws/2021/03/31/brand-personality-messaging">brand messaging</a> will likely shift in multiple ways to appeal to consumers as they cautiously reemerge from not only a pandemic, but a <a href="/blog/ws/2021/03/19/prepare-for-recession">recession</a>, and face an ongoing climate crisis and racial justice movement.</span></p>
<p><span lang="EN">Naturally, there is no one-size-fits-all guidance here, but there are some overarching themes.</span></p>
<h3><span lang="EN">Celebrate the move forward but donâ€™t forget the past</span></h3>
<p><span lang="EN">For starters, brands should be sensitive to â€œthose financially, emotionally and physically <a href="/blog/ws/2020/03/13/covid-19-response">affected by the pandemic</a>,â€ said Devin Johnson, CEO of <a href="/blog/ws/2021/04/21/cost-effective-marketing-automation-tools-small-businesses">marketing automation</a> software company<span lang="EN"> <a href="https://kennected.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Kennected</a><span lang="EN">.</span></span></span></p>
<p><span lang="EN">Juan Pablo Sarmiento, CEO of content network<span lang="EN"> <a href="https://www.bypeople.com/">ByPeople.com</a><span lang="EN">, agreed brand messages must be â€œsoftened, more human and less machine-like.â€</span></span></span></p>
<p><span lang="EN">For Brand Hopperâ€™s Cassidy, itâ€™s striking a balance between â€œthe realization the past year has been difficult for many and some experienced serious lossâ€ and â€œexcitement as we get back to a sense of normalcy.â€</span></p>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="7a345221-c6c5-44df-bbc6-dde1e6f20848" data-langcode="en">
