</div>
<p><span lang="EN">Meanwhile, standard video content remains a solid strategy, tooâ€”and that includes digital <a href="/blog/ws/2012/11/27/youtube-advertising">advertising on platforms like YouTube</a> as consumer <a href="/blog/ws/2017/03/08/video-marketing-statistics">appetite for video</a> remains.</span></p>
<p><span lang="EN">Per <span lang="EN">figures from Dustin Porreca, SEO manager at B2B marketing agency <span lang="EN"><a href="https://www.elevatedemand.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Elevate Demand</a><span lang="EN">, clients have seen an average 68% increase in video content consumption on YouTube since March 2020 (more <a href="/blog/ws/2021/06/17/post-pandemic-digital-marketing-statistics">post-covid stats here</a>).</span></span></span></span></p>
<p><span lang="EN">â€œYouTube provides an opportunity to explain your products or services in detail and provide the authenticity users are looking for,â€ <span lang="EN">added John McGhee, owner of digital agency <a href="https://www.webconsuls.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Webconsuls</a><span lang="EN">.</span></span></span></p>
<h2>5. Keep investing in social</h2>
<p><span lang="EN">Social media is another trend that isnâ€™t going to go awayâ€”although the <a href="/blog/ws/2019/03/19/social-media-for-small-business">specific channels marketers use</a> may shift.</span></p>
<h3><strong><span lang="EN">Continue on your existing channels</span></strong></h3>
<p><span lang="EN">Even when the world opens back up again, consumers will continue to use their favorite platforms, which Porreca said justifies continued investment.</span></p>
<p><span lang="EN">â€œIn any marketing strategy, your goal is meeting your buyers where they&#8217;re going to be at any given time,â€ he said.</span></p>
<h3><span lang="EN">Consider TikTok or Clubhouse</span></h3>
<p><span lang="EN">In addition to YouTube and Facebook, which a recent study fromÂ <span lang="EN"><a href="https://www.pewresearch.org/internet/2021/04/07/social-media-use-in-2021/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Pew Research Center</a><span lang="EN"> shows are the most popular platforms with U.S. consumers overall, brands would be wise to turn their attention to video-sharing platform <a href="/blog/ws/2020/08/11/advertising-on-tiktok">TikTok</a>, which<span lang="EN"> reportedly saw usage climbÂ <a href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/johnkoetsier/2020/09/14/massive-tiktok-growth-up-75-this-year-now-33x-more-users-than-nearest-competitor/?sh=3fbacd044fe4">75%</a>Â in 2020,<span lang="EN">Â as well as another up-and-comer, audio-based app Clubhouse.</span></span></span></span></span></p>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="6e0f569a-60f8-4ab5-a68f-1a5cf4474a4a" data-langcode="en">
