</div>
<p class="text-align-center"><span lang="EN"><a href="https://blog.shuttlerock.com/complete-guide-to-tiktok-video-ad-formats" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Image source</em></a></span></p>
<p><em><span lang="EN">`</span></em><span lang="EN">â€œA little-known secret is you can get great results in some industries by <a href="/blog/ws/2020/07/22/tiktok-ads">advertising on TikTok</a>,â€ said <span lang="EN">Dennis Consorte, small business consultant at review site <span lang="EN"><a href="http://digital.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Digital.com</a><span lang="EN">. <span lang="EN">â€œThere isnâ€™t much competition, so ad costs are relatively low.â€</span></span></span></span></span></p>
<h2>6. Take advantage of lower CPCs</h2>
<p><span lang="EN">Speaking of lower costs, while digital platforms remained an important avenue to reach home-bound consumers during the pandemic, Timothy Robinson, CEO of review site <span lang="EN"><a href="https://invpn.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">InVPN</a><span lang="EN">, pointed to dropping <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/02/02/cpc-landing-page-optimization">CPC</a> prices in the coming months. </span></span></span></p>
<p><span lang="EN">This, he said, presents an opportunity to reach customers online at even lower costsâ€”even if brands themselves have faced budget cuts.</span></p>
<p><span lang="EN">â€œOther advertisers are likely to go offline at this time, allowing companies to <a href="/blog/ws/2014/08/14/increase-traffic-to-my-website">capture more traffic</a> and conversions,â€ he said.</span></p>
<p><span lang="EN"><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nealtaparia/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Neal Taparia</a>â€”entrepreneur, investor, and co-founder of <a href="https://spider-solitaire-challenge.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Spider Solitaire Challenge</a>â€”<span lang="EN">agreed, noting <a href="/blog/ws/2016/10/17/ppc-formulas">PPC advertising</a> is â€œ<span lang="EN">a great way of maintaining additional presence online, as well as reminding your customers that your business is going strong.â€</span></span></span></p>
<h2>7. Continue optimizing for local</h2>
<p><span lang="EN"><a href="https://localiq.com/local-marketing-lab" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Local marketing</a> has arguably been <a href="/blog/ws/2020/05/08/seo-during-covid-19">more important in the last 12 months than ever before</a>â€”and that, too, will continue.</span></p>
<h3><span lang="EN">Assume continued #shoplocal support</span></h3>
<p><span lang="EN">Per Amy Dixon, digital marketing manager of digital agency<span lang="EN"> <a href="https://www.hydracreative.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hydra Creative</a><span lang="EN">, this is because of â€œa huge positive change in attitudes towards local businessesâ€ during the pandemic, which is expected to continue after lockdown. In the U.K. for example, <a href="https://startupsmagazine.co.uk/article-google-finds-we-are-economy-kindness" target="_blank" rel="noopener">38%</a> of consumers <span lang="EN">reportedly shopped more at small businesses in 2020<span lang="EN">â€”and 88% say they are more likely to shop locally moving forward.</span></span></span></span></span></p>
<h3><span lang="EN">Run online and offline campaigns</span></h3>
<p><span lang="EN">As a result, marketers should continue to optimize for â€œnear meâ€ searches and <a href="/blog/ws/2020/07/16/how-to-ask-for-reviews">solicit customer reviews</a>. But they should also consider local media like radio ads, which <span lang="EN">Sabrina Beaumont, CMO of house plan site<span lang="EN"> <a href="https://passionplans.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Passion Plans</a><span lang="EN">, said she intends to do to â€œhopefully allow us to gain some local goodwillâ€ in the markets in which she operates.</span></span></span></span></p>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="5e34557e-5034-4a98-8a02-7247b1a74533" data-langcode="en">
<article>
<div><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/inspiring-post-pandemic-marketing-ideas-local-seo-1.png" alt="inspiring post-covid marketing ideas show up in near me searches" width="733" height="539" /></div>
</article>
</div>
<p class="text-align-center"><em>Your <a href="/blog/ws/2020/06/08/what-is-google-my-business">Google Business Profile</a> is the key to showing up in &#8220;near me&#8221; and Maps searches.</em></p>
<p><span lang="EN">Whether or not workers return to offices full-time remains to be seen. In the meantime, <span lang="EN">Solomon Thimothy, co-founder of marketing dashboard<span lang="EN"> <a href="https://www.clickx.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Clickx</a><span lang="EN">, agreed marketers should focus on â€œall things localâ€ as â€œmost people will continue to work from home even when they can already go back to the office.â€</span></span></span></span></p>
<p><span lang="EN">In a similar vein, Iversen said he stopped sponsoring <a href="/blog/ws/2018/06/05/podcast-advertising">podcasts</a> when commuters stopped going to offices. But that, too, could provide a new opportunity for brands as consumers return to work.</span></p>
<h2><span lang="EN">Use these post-pandemic marketing ideas to come back stronger than ever</span></h2>
<p>And there you have it. Data-based, industry expert-given tips to meet your customers where they&#8217;re at as the world starts to reopen. Let&#8217;s quickly recap:</p>
<ol>
<li>Return to out-of-home advertising and live events</li>
<li>Adjust for empathetic brand messaging</li>
<li>Make your brand&#8217;s stance clear</li>
<li>Keep pushing video</li>
<li>Continue investing in social</li>
<li>Take advantage of lower CPCs</li>
<li>Stay focused on local marketing</li>
</ol>
