<h3>2. Prepare for the end of third-party cookies</h3>
<p>2021 will also be the year marketers prepare for two big changes to come in 2022: the end of third-party cookies and new <a href="/blog/ws/2014/10/08/online-privacy">privacy</a> regulations in California.</p>
<p>â€œWe have to get comfortable with privacy-first data collection practices. That meansÂ focusing on list-building and developing one-to-one relationships with customers,â€ said Harry Maugans, CEO of consumer privacy service <a href="https://privacybee.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Privacy Bee</a>. â€œMake sure that your campaigns in 2021 help you build your first-party data so you rely less on Other People&#8217;s Data.â€</p>
