<p>â€œThe pandemic will have a profound and lasting impact on customer mindset andÂ messaging that focuses solely on <a href="/blog/ws/2020/07/29/how-to-promote-a-product">product or service</a> instead of compassion and trust will not fly,â€ Wood said. â€œSince our business already has a focus on safety,<strong>Â </strong>tweaking our message to be about cleanliness and peace of mind will be an ongoing strategy through 2021.â€</p>
<h3>8. Grow communities</h3>
<p>In addition to demonstrating they are trustworthy, brands should foster communities of<a href="/blog/ws/2016/11/10/customer-loyalty"> loyal customers</a> in 2021.</p>
<p>â€œThe notion of community building isn&#8217;t novel, but brands in 2021 need to understand that loyalty is coming back and brands that know what it is their customers want, as well as how to engage them through transparency and humility, is what will become the difference maker,â€ said SEO consultant Itamar Blauer.</p>
<p>Olga Petrik, CMO of Gmail CRM firm <a href="https://nethunt.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NetHunt CRM</a>, agreed brands should invest more in loyalty and <a href="/blog/ws/2018/03/13/ecommerce-retention">retention</a> for 2021.</p>
<p>â€œTheir existing customer base has come this far with them throughout the pandemicâ€”itâ€™s stable to some extent,â€ she said. â€œBy switching from customer support to a customer success strategy, a business can ensure that customers receive maximum value from a product.</p>
<h3>9. Optimize for voice search</h3>
<p>Weâ€™ve seen <a href="/blog/ws/2018/02/15/voice-search-seo">voice search</a> in previous year-end predictions. However, 2021 may be the year it really takes off as consumers used their voice-enabled devices more while they were at home during the pandemic.</p>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="cbbe39bb-5690-47de-afaf-0e3264fdf15c" data-langcode="en">
