</div>
<p>â€œThis in turn meant people were more willing to explore what their smart home devices could do and open a dialogue with them and begin to learn and rely on them,â€ said Polly Kay, senior marketing manager at window covering retailer <a href="https://www.englishblinds.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">English Blinds</a>.</p>
<p>As a result, brands should optimize for voice search by focusing on longer-tail keywords that reflect how consumers ask questions or make requests verbally to stay ahead of the curve.</p>
<p>â€œMuch [like] Google introduced mobile-first ranking for SEO even in instances of user searches on desktop devices, so, too, is it highly likely that as the popularity of voice search queries increases, Google [will] place a heavier weighting on ranking and rewarding content that successfully meets the needs of voice searchers,â€ she added.</p>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="c8435509-f9f8-4f55-bda8-f6678122da79" data-langcode="en">
