<p>â€œAt the end of each campaign it will test, <a href="/blog/ws/2017/08/28/behavioral-segmentation">segment</a>,Â and analyze conversions,â€ he said. â€œThis leavesÂ you with huge time savings<strong>Â </strong>and allows you to focus solely on monitoring the results and optimizing to improve future performance.â€</p>
<p>And David Kolodny, cofounder of startup studio <a href="https://www.wilburlabs.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Wilbur Labs</a>, noted the value of automation and real-time data skyrocketed in 2020 because it was so important to understand what was happening in the momentâ€”and itâ€™s impossible for manual processes to keep up with such rapid change.</p>
<p>â€œThough trends are smoother now than they were in March and April, we are still seeing rapid customer behavior changes on a daily basis and real-time data loops have directly contributed to greater marketing efficiencies,â€ Kolodny said. â€œBy utilizing automation wherever applicableâ€” and connecting it to real-time dataâ€”we have been able to ensure that our portfolio companies are maximizing every opportunity available to them. Real-time data and automation will be the difference between companies that excel in 2021 and those that are left behind.â€</p>
